<rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/" version="2.0"><channel><title>Personal Combined Feed</title><link>https://example.invalid</link><description>Personal aggregate feed</description><docs>http://www.rssboard.org/rss-specification</docs><generator>python-feedgen</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 12:22:11 +0000</lastBuildDate><item><title>Ask HN: I hate you. Don't leave me (the AI edition)</title><link>https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48322092</link><description>&lt;p&gt;How often do you guys receive emails (and other messages, too) that are obviously written entirely by AI? You know the type… those hollow contrast phrases like "This isn't about X, it's about Y."&lt;p&gt;But more importantly: how often do you send emails and other messages written entirely by AI?&lt;/p&gt;
